Comprehensive training on how to use Simulink, a graphical simulation tool for modeling dynamic physical systems. The course is self-paced and interactive, with hands-on exercises in Simulink.

Learn how to incrementally build and validate power systems using Simscape Electrical.
Learn how to perform model-based systems engineering by creating simulatable architecture models using System Composer.
Learn the basics of simulating battery systems in Simscape.

Learn how to model algorithms in Simulink, visualize and analyze simulation results, and read and write data with Simulink. The Simulink Fundamentals course is divided into five parts. This first part builds on the skills learned in Simulink Onramp course.\n\nThis is part of the Simulink Fundamentals course.

Model and simulate continuous and discrete dynamic systems in Simulink. Learn how to model differential and difference equations, incorporate transfer function and state-space representations, and simulate physical boundaries and multirate systems.\n\n This is part of the Simulink Fundamentals course.
Create visual and functional hierarchy within a model using Subsystems. Control the execution of subsystems using other signals in your model.\n\n This is part of the Simulink Fundamentals course.
Organize larger projects by referencing other models and creating libraries. Learn how to unit test and accelerate referenced models.\n\n This is part of the Simulink Fundamentals course.

Learn how to improve simulation performance and troubleshoot common performance issues. See how Simulink solves models under various conditions.\n\n This is the final part of the Simulink Fundamentals course.
